---
title: BeaconLink Agent Registration Sequence
---

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Agent as BeaconLink Agent
    participant Relay as Relay Network
    participant Gateway as API Gateway
    participant Auth as Identity Provider
    participant PKI as Certificate Authority
    participant Policy as Policy Engine
    participant Control as BeaconLink Control Plane
    participant Inventory as Inventory Service
    participant Scheduler as Distributed Scheduler
    participant Events as Event Streaming Platform
    participant Audit as Audit Service

    %% =====================================================
    %% Agent Initialization
    %% =====================================================

    Note over Agent: Agent starts with issued identity<br/>certificate and bootstrap configuration

    Agent->>Agent: Load configuration
    Agent->>Agent: Load X.509 certificate
    Agent->>Agent: Initialize secure storage

    %% =====================================================
    %% Secure Network Connection
    %% =====================================================

    Agent->>Relay: Establish outbound mTLS connection
    Relay->>PKI: Validate certificate chain
    PKI-->>Relay: Certificate valid

    Relay-->>Agent: Secure session established

    %% =====================================================
    %% Registration Request
    %% =====================================================

    Agent->>Gateway: Registration request
    Note right of Agent: Includes:\n• Agent ID\n• Site ID\n• Certificate\n• Runtime Version\n• Capabilities

    Gateway->>Auth: Authenticate machine identity
    Auth->>PKI: Validate certificate
    PKI-->>Auth: Identity trusted
    Auth-->>Gateway: Authentication successful

    %% =====================================================
    %% Authorization
    %% =====================================================

    Gateway->>Policy: Evaluate registration policy

    Note right of Policy: Validate:\n• Site authorization\n• Agent identity\n• Organization policy\n• Certificate trust\n• Registration limits

    Policy-->>Gateway: Registration permitted

    %% =====================================================
    %% Control Plane Registration
    %% =====================================================

    Gateway->>Control: Forward authenticated registration

    Control->>Inventory: Register managed site
    Control->>Inventory: Register agent
    Control->>Inventory: Store runtime capabilities

    Inventory-->>Control: Registration persisted

    %% =====================================================
    %% Scheduler Integration
    %% =====================================================

    Control->>Scheduler: Notify available execution node
    Scheduler-->>Control: Scheduler updated

    %% =====================================================
    %% Initial Synchronization
    %% =====================================================

    Control->>Agent: Registration successful

    Control->>Agent: Desired State
    Control->>Agent: Policy Bundle
    Control->>Agent: Relay Configuration
    Control->>Agent: Reconciliation Configuration

    Agent->>Agent: Persist configuration
    Agent->>Agent: Start reconciliation loop

    %% =====================================================
    %% Event Publication
    %% =====================================================

    Control->>Events: Publish AgentRegistered
    Control->>Audit: Record registration

    Events-->>Scheduler: Registration notification
    Events-->>Inventory: Inventory update
    Events-->>Policy: Registration event

    %% =====================================================
    %% Continuous Operation
    %% =====================================================

    loop Continuous Registration Validation

        Agent->>Relay: Heartbeat

        Relay->>Control: Forward heartbeat

        Control->>Policy: Validate active identity
        Policy-->>Control: Authorized

        Control-->>Agent: Desired state updates (if changed)

    end

    %% =====================================================
    %% Registration Failure Path
    %% =====================================================

    alt Authentication or Policy Failure

        Gateway-->>Agent: Registration rejected

        Gateway->>Audit: Record failed registration

        Gateway->>Events: Publish AgentRegistrationFailed

        Agent->>Agent: Backoff and retry

    else Registration Successful

        Note over Agent,Control: Agent becomes an active,<br/>trusted execution node capable of<br/>receiving deployments and workflow tasks.

    end